description.narrative: UNICEF;supported national and subnational capacity strengthening for better access to essential services for children victims and/or at risk of;violence, abuse and exploitation, through awareness-raising on social norms and available services. Essential services were offered to 2,698 children.;With regard to children in conflict with the law (CICL), support was given to implementing partners (TDH Italy and IMED);to facilitate access to courts and ensure the release of 42 minors. In addition, 113 juvenile justice system actors received training on procedures and legal protection. The juvenile justice sector currently has a validated SOP that allows actors to ensure quality treatment of CICL. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/01/2022
